Description: Handle sliver of a Rhodian pottery transport amphora at neck join. Clay fine pink-buff. Circular stamp with rose symbol.
Curator's comments: Petrie Diary (EES Archive XVII 47) p. 182, 1? Name Timagoras. From same die as Alexandria, Greco-Roman Museum, ABC 0219.33.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (JB.1152)
